{"id":"salmon","term":"Salmon","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>Garment, the son of Nashon (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Ruth 4:20\">Ruth 4:20</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Matthew 1:4\">Matt. 1:4</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Matthew 1:5\">5</a>), possibly the same as Salma in <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Chronicles 2:51\">1 Chr. 2:51</a>.</p>\n\u0000","refs":["Ruth 4:20","Matthew 1:4","Matthew 1:5","1 Chronicles 2:51"]}